{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/principle/push-to-deploy","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.‚Äã\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ‚ÄãConference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"b787665f-384e-5b56-a2cb-a87123f53ddb","name":"push-to-deploy","relativeDirectory":"post/principle","relativePath":"post/principle/push-to-deploy.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/5QhcSEBZKb73yIoJitpiW9/bec388aed57a5d29620a08a1c63304c7/snowflake-push-to-deploy.svg?w=1368&h=1239","alt":"Snowflake: Push to deploy"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://coderbyheart.github.io/snowflake/#156:473,302:241,369:56,392:45,396:86,465:116","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"My most blissful hours as a software engineer are those where I can\nuninterruptedly focus on an implementation task. It's a "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"joyful"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" state of mind,\nwhich is called "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The Zone"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", and it means for me to be able to concentrate for a\nprolonged time on a specific detail or problem. This phase is then concluded,\nwhen the feature is complete, the tests are green and the changes are pushed to\nthe repository. I can now make a coffee and think about the next "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"new thing"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" to\nwork on."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"What I don't want is to spend time waiting for my change to be deployed, or\nworse deploy them manually. This involves boring, tedious, repetitive steps\nwhich have to be executed in a specific order. Computers are great at this, they\nhave an unlimited amount of patience and are perfect at executing instructions\nin a given order."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Automating deployment processes implictly creates "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"living documentation"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" of the\nsystems needed to put changes in front of consumers, and therefore adds\nresilience to any software project. The instructions how to deploy the project\nare always up to date, because they "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"do"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" the deployment."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I spent a significant amount of time in enabling and maintaining deployments,\nhowever in my experience is this time wisely invested in times where I could\nplan it, and allowes me to move fast in times of crisis."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Push to deploy"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" requires "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"confidence to deploy"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". This confidence is created by\nusing techniques like test-driven-development, end-to-end testing, static code\nanalysis and others to ensure that run-time defects to not happen often and that\na change. Those are first-principles in their own right which I will focus in\nlater posts."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#busfactor--","ariaLabel":"busfactor   permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"busFactor = ‚àû"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"busfactor--","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Push to deploy is a way to increase the\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"bus factor"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bus_factor","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"t